The fastest animal on land is the **cheetah**, which can reach speeds of up to **70 mph (113 km/h)**. However, if we're talking about the fastest animal overall, including air and water, it's a different story.

The fastest animal in the world is actually the **peregrine falcon**, which can dive at speeds of up to **242 mph (390 km/h)** during its characteristic hunting dive, known as a stoop. This makes it not only the fastest bird but also the fastest member of the animal kingdom!

Other fast animals include:

* Pronghorn antelope: up to 60 mph (97 km/h)
* Lion: up to 50 mph (80 km/h)
* Sailfish: up to 68 mph (110 km/h) in water
* Bluefin tuna: up to 35 mph (56 km/h) in water

But remember, speed can vary depending on the context and method of measurement. The peregrine falcon's incredible diving speed is still the record holder, though!
